# 🤖 ResumeAI — Resume Analyzer + Interview Simulator

A full-stack AI-powered web app that analyzes your resume and simulates job interviews with instant feedback. Built with **Python Flask** + **Three.js** + **glassmorphism UI**.

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.8+-blue) ![Flask](https://img.shields.io/badge/Flask-3.0-green) ![Three.js](https://img.shields.io/badge/Three.js-r128-orange)

---

## ✨ Features

### 📄 Resume Analyzer
- Upload your PDF resume (or try the demo mode)
- AI extracts skills across 5 categories: Programming, Web, Data/AI, Cloud/DevOps, Soft Skills
- Match score against 6 job roles (Software Engineer, Data Scientist, DevOps, etc.)
- Animated score ring with visual feedback
- Personalized improvement suggestions

### 🎤 Interview Simulator
- Generates personalized questions based on your resume skills
- Behavioral, Technical, and Role-Specific questions
- 2-minute countdown timer per question
- AI evaluates your answer and gives:
  - Score (0–100) + letter grade
  - Specific strengths
  - Concrete improvement tips
- Final performance dashboard with score breakdown

### 🎨 UI/UX
- Glassmorphism card design
- Three.js 3D animated background (particles + floating wireframe geometry)
- Mouse parallax effect on 3D scene
- Smooth CSS animations and transitions
- Fully responsive (mobile + desktop)
- Animated score counters and progress rings

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Backend | Python Flask |
| Resume Parsing | PyPDF2 |
| NLP / Scoring | Custom keyword extraction |
| 3D Animation | Three.js (r128) |
| UI Design | Glassmorphism CSS |
| Typography | Syne + Space Grotesk (Google Fonts) |
| Deployment | Gunicorn + Render/Railway compatible |

---

## 🚀 Setup & Run

### Prerequisites
- Python 3.8+
- pip

### 1. Clone the repository
```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/resume-ai-app.git
cd resume-ai-app
```

### 2. Install dependencies
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

### 3. Run the app
```bash
python app.py
```

### 4. Open in browser
```
http://localhost:5000
```

